node.text: Becky gives you a glimpse at her favorite cookbook. What’s your favorite cookbook?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 19, 2021. May be an image of chicken sandwich.

node.text: Crunchy, juicy, and slicked with mayo, a spicy fried chicken sandwich is a lunchtime favorite, but we aren't about to heat up a skillet of frying oil whenever the craving strikes. In this version, we use our air fryer to get the job done. Air-Fryer Spicy Fried Chicken Sandwich recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 19, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Fajitas are a sizzling spectacle, but we wanted a recipe that was more about flavor than theater and used only one baking sheet. Tap the link in our profile for our One-Pan Steak Fajitas recipe.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 19, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: We set out to make a smooth, creamy, cheesy sauce without the bother of a béchamel or custard. Making the whole dish in just 20 minutes was a bonus. Simple Stovetop Macaroni and Cheese recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 18, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: The components of a Linzertorte couldn’t be easier to prepare. A buttery, nut-enhanced crust comes together easily in the food processor, and the raspberry jam filling is something you buy. Tap the link in our profile for our Linzertorte recipe.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 18, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Cure and smoke pork belly and you’ve got bacon. Roast the belly instead and you’ve got the ultimate pork entrée—provided the meat is tender and the skin stunningly crisp. Crispy Slow Roasted Pork Belly recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 18, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Miso is one of the best ways to flavor salmon—inside and out. Tap the link in our profile for our fan-favorite recipe for Miso-Marinated Salmon.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 18, 2021.

node.text: You no longer need to fear the drudgery of peeling hard-cooked eggs—with the right cooking method, the shells practically fly off. Easy-Peel Hard-Cooked Eggs recipe link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by America's Test Kitchen on September 17, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: Repurpose one of your favorite savory ingredients for a cake that’s light yet plush and simple yet sophisticated. Tap the link in our profile for our Olive Oil Cake recipe.

node.text: We have tested almost every size and type of skillet out there, from cast iron to carbon steel to nonstick and more. Tap the link in our bio to watch the full video on YouTube.

node.text: Provençal vegetable soup is a classic French summer soup with a delicate broth that is intensified by a dollop of pistou, the French equivalent of Italy’s pesto. We wanted a simple version that focused on fresh seasonal vegetables. Get our recipe by clicking the link in our profile.
